# General Coding Standards

## Code Style

### JavaScript
- **ES6+ syntax** (classes, arrow functions, async/await)
- **2 spaces** indentation
- **Semicolons** required
- **Single quotes** for strings (unless escaping needed)
- **camelCase** for variables and functions
- **PascalCase** for classes

### YAML
- **2 spaces** indentation (no tabs)
- **Quotes** for strings with special characters
- **Consistent structure** across data files

### CSS
- **2 spaces** indentation
- **kebab-case** for class names
- **CSS variables** for theming
- **Mobile-first** responsive design

## Error Handling

### JavaScript
```javascript
try {
    // operation
} catch (error) {
    console.error('Error:', error);
    // User-friendly error message
    this.terminal.write(`\x1b[1;31mError: ${error.message}\x1b[0m\r\n`);
}
```

### Null/Undefined Checks
- Use optional chaining: `obj?.prop?.nested`
- Check existence before access: `if (data) { ... }`
- Provide defaults: `const value = data?.value || 'default'`

## Performance

### JavaScript
- **Avoid blocking operations** in main thread
- **Use async/await** for I/O operations
- **Debounce/throttle** frequent events
- **Lazy load** heavy resources

### CSS
- **Use transform/opacity** for animations
- **Minimize repaints/reflows**
- **Optimize selectors** (avoid deep nesting)

### Terminal
- **Limit scrollback** (1000 lines default)
- **Batch terminal writes** when possible
- **Use efficient formatting** utilities

## Security

### Data Validation
- **Validate user input** before processing
- **Sanitize paths** in filesystem operations
- **Check permissions** before file access

### External Resources
- **Use HTTPS** for external resources
- **Validate API responses** before use
- **Handle API errors** gracefully

## Documentation

### Code Comments
- **Explain why**, not what
- **Document complex logic**
- **Note non-obvious behavior**
- **Mark TODOs** for future work

### Function Documentation
