 * Executes a terminal command
 * @param {string} command - Command name
 * @param {Array} args - Command arguments
 * @returns {Promise<void>}
 */
async runCommand(command, args) {
    // Implementation
}
```

## Testing

### Manual Testing
- Test all commands locally
- Verify responsive design
- Check cross-browser compatibility
- Test error scenarios

### Browser Support
- **Chrome/Edge** (primary)
- **Firefox** (secondary)
- **Safari** (tertiary)
- **Mobile browsers** (responsive)

## Git Practices

### Commit Messages
- **Clear, descriptive** messages
- **Present tense** ("Add feature" not "Added feature")
- **Reference issues** if applicable

### Branch Strategy
- **main** branch for production
- **Feature branches** for development (if needed)
- **No force push** to main

## Dependencies

### External Libraries
- **xterm.js** - Terminal emulator (CDN)
- **Jekyll plugins** - Ruby gems
- **Minimal Mistakes** - Jekyll theme

### Version Management
- **Gemfile** for Ruby dependencies
- **No package.json** (vanilla JS)
- **CDN links** for JavaScript libraries

## Accessibility

### Keyboard Navigation
- **Tab completion** for commands
- **Arrow keys** for history
- **Ctrl+F** for search
- **ESC** to skip boot

### Screen Readers
- **Semantic HTML** in layouts
- **ARIA labels** where needed
- **Alt text** for images

## Browser Compatibility

### Feature Detection
```javascript
if (window.FeatureName) {
    // Use feature
} else {
    // Fallback
}
```

### Polyfills
- Use only when necessary
- Prefer native features
- Test fallbacks

